==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refutation
<hw>Ref`u*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(r?f`?*t?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>refutatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧futation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act or process of refuting or disproving, or the state of being
refuted; proof of falsehood or error; the overthrowing of an argument,
opinion, testimony, doctrine, or theory, by argument or countervailing
proof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Same of his blunders seem rather to deserve a flogging than a
<qex>refutation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refutatory</ent>⟦br⟧
